Nandi Senator Samson Cherargei at a past press conference in Parliament, Nairobi [David Njaaga, Standard]  A senator has called for the investigation of top officials of an agency for alleged favouritism in road projects.  In a statement to the Senate Committee on Roads and Transportation, Samson Cherargei of Nandi said the Kenya Urban Roads Authority (Kura) had sidelined Rift Valley counties.  “KURA should list for us the all the contracts that they have executed in the last three years, the companies allocated, regions where the projects are and in which counties are they spread,” said Cherargei.    How call from a jilted lover ignited a vicious war at giant audit firm  Lifestyle Audit Bill won't end graft because no politician can survive without corruption  Mandatory lifestyle audit for public officials gets nod  MPs cannot account for millions of NG-CDF funds  Mini Polls Audit: Political temperatures rising, recent by-elections marred by reports of violence  KEMSA Theft: Auditor General's report on KEMSA, suspect tender firms in scam named  Next Auditor General: President nominates Nancy Janet Kabui Gathungu as Auditor General By Kennedy Gachuhi | 1 hour ago By Kennedy Gachuhi | 10 hours ago By Phares Mutembei | 21 hours ago By Lynn Kolongei | 1 day ago